<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 27 at 4:26AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM...
An area of snow will continue across the area through the mid
morning hours. Brief intervals of heavier snow may develop at
times, leading to accumulation of one to two inches in some
locations. This will lead to some roads becoming snow covered,
particularly secondary roads, bridges and overpasses. In addition,
visibility may drop below 2 miles at times. Use caution while
driving this morning and allow extra time to reach your
destination. Be prepared for variable road conditions and lowered
visibilities through the morning commute.</description>
